parse: Verb - Aorist Participle Active - Nominative Masculine Plural
str2: To cross over, pass over. From dia and a derivative of the base of peran; to cross entirely.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Active - 3rd Person Plural

str2: A primary preposition; to or into, of place, time, or purpose; also in adverbial phrases.
Of Hebrew origin; Gennesaret, a lake and plain in Palestine.

parse: Verb - Aorist Indicative Passive - 3rd Person Plural
str2: I anchor at a place. From pros and a derivative of the same as horme (anchor) or lull); to moor to, i.e. land at.
